sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT line_id) 
FROM pio_lines
WHERE pio_id IN (SELECT pio_id FROM pio_ports WHERE port_type = 'GPIO');

SELECT COUNT(instance_id) 
FROM peripheral_instances 
WHERE mcu_type = 'STM32F4';

external_knowledge:
- 'Configuration version' refers to different versions of a specific configuration;
- 'Average version number' is calculated across all configuration versions;
- 'More than one version' means the user has accessed or used more than one distinct version of the configuration.

- 'Analog-to-Digital Converter' is a type of peripheral instance, often referred to as 'ADC';
- 'Majority' means more than 50%;
- 'Most recent configurations' are determined by the latest creation timestamp.

- 'Most recent' configuration is determined by the highest `config_id` within each project;
- 'Initialization' refers to the type of configuration;
- 'Active' status indicates the configuration is currently in use.

- "Gardens with many blooming flowers" refers to projects with a high number of configurations;
- "More than one version on average" means the average version number of configurations is greater than 1;
- "High rate of edits" implies that more than half of the access events are edits.

sql:
SELECT pio_name, description
FROM pio_ports
WHERE num_lines = 8;

SELECT pio_name, num_lines
FROM pio_ports
ORDER BY num_lines DESC;

external_knowledge:
- Configurations represent different setups or configurations within a project;
- Versions represent different iterations or updates of a configuration;
- Accesses represent the number of times a configuration has been accessed or used.

sql:
SELECT pin_name
FROM peripheral_pins
WHERE pin_type = 'output';

external_knowledge:
- Active configurations are those with a status of 'active';
- The most frequently accessed configuration is determined by the highest number of access events;
- Each peripheral instance can have multiple configurations, but only one is selected as the most accessed.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(config_id) 
FROM peripheral_configurations 
WHERE project_id IN (SELECT project_id FROM projects WHERE status = 'in progress');

SELECT user_id, access_type
FROM access_logs
WHERE access_id < 10;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT pin_id) AS unique_pins, COUNT(DISTINCT instance_id) AS unique_instances
FROM peripheral_configurations
WHERE configuration_type = 'initialization' AND status = 'active';

external_knowledge:
- "peripheral instances" refer to unique identifiers for each peripheral in the system;
- "pins" are the unique identifiers for each peripheral pin;
- "adorned with the latest version" means that the configuration version is the most recent one;
- "bloom with the approval of the keepers" implies that the configuration version has been approved and accessed recently;
- "keepers" refer to the users who have accessed the configurations.

- 'sprouted' refers to the presence of configurations;
- 'blooming flowers' refers to active configurations;
- 'more than one' indicates the count of configurations is greater than one.

- 'STM32F4' is a type of microcontroller unit (MCU) used in various embedded systems;
- 'Project Alpha' is a specific project name that refers to a particular set of configurations and instances;
- 'Developers' are users with the role of creating and managing configurations in the system;
- 'View' access type indicates that the users have read-only access to the configurations.

- 'Project A' is a specific project in the database;
- 'Analog-to-Digital Converter' is a type of peripheral instance;
- 'Line 8 of Port A' is a specific PIO line name;
- The most recently approved version is determined by the latest approval date.

- 'garden of ongoing projects' refers to projects with a status of 'in progress';
- 'names of the flowers' refers to the project names;
- 'budding parts' refers to the peripheral instance names;
- 'type of care they receive' refers to the configuration type;
- 'budding' refers to the project status being 'in progress';
- 'first touch of water' refers to the configuration type 'initialization';
- 'ongoing nourishment' refers to the configuration type 'runtime'.
